Things happen suddenly, and thus I write:
This is the <@act.missionTips>first time</> the nine-tailed child will join battle.
By harnessing her unique Arts,
<@act.missionTips>the enemy will never be able to touch those devices</>.

Do not rely on any external power.
They will only tarnish the purity of your Arts.
At the moment <@act.missionTips>anger boils over</>,
<@act.missionTips>discard the power of the devices</> and make your stand.

The morning mist compels the quill.
The <@act.missionTips>stones of Wolumonde</> congregate, then disintegrate.
Until <@act.missionTips>20 Colossi are returned to the earth</>,
the land shall know no respite.

<@act.missionTips>Beneath the Capitol Spire</>.
<@act.missionTips>Mudrock's</> Sarkaz decide to act.
A tongue of flame laps at the whole town.
But in front of the gates, no more than <@act.missionTips>6 people</> stand guard.

At the end of it all, consciousness begins to escape from my mind.
I saw the town I once hated riddled with holes, but this brought me no joy.
The ones left behind <@act.missionTips>continue their search into the wilderness, and find a new conflict</>.
There, I see <@act.missionTips>three wandering giants</>.
I see our mountain.

camp_AliveUntilSunset.campDesc:
Alive Until Sunset, a.k.a. AUS. 
Despite its popularity, the identities of this famous heavy metal band's members are well-kept secrets. Although initially obscure, the band soon entered a contract with Monster Siren Records, and their first album, Deep Color in the Sea, immediately became a smash hit after release, securing their status as a top band within their genre. Unlike many of of the other bands in the scene that have been shunned by mainstream listeners, AUS keeps their lyrics completely clean.

camp_DDD.campDesc:
Destructive Dragon Demon, or D.D.D. in short, 
is a famed electronic music producer and DJ whose face is always hidden behind a mask. Their real identity has remained a secret since their debut. Humorous and energizing, D.D.D.'s title song went viral on the city's social media platform almost overnight, and their name soon spread across nearby cities, soaring to the top spot as song of the year among Messengers and becoming a modern internet miracle.

camp_Emperor.campDesc:
Also known as 'The Monarch,' 'The King,' and 'Big E.' 
Record producer of Monster Siren Records, senior rap star of Columbia, and entrepreneur.Nominated in several major music awards. Emperor is known for his unshakable status among rappers in western Columbia and his massive investments and entrepreneurial success. His private life, however, is always kept from the public eye, and he himself is very difficult to reach. Emperor has not released any new songs in a while, perhaps due to the demands of his other businesses.

news_1.newsTitle: The 4 cities of Kawalerielki have successfully docked together, raising the curtain on the Kazimierz Major
news_1.newsText:
June 10: Following the completion of the docking checks, 'The Grand Knight's Territory' Kawalerielki, the grandest city of Kazimierz, is once again revealed to the world. Before the end of the Major, the combined city of Kawalerielki formed from four separate cities shall remain one of the grandest nomadic cities on Terra. The union of the four cities also proclaims the official start of the Kazimierz Major.

news_8.newsTitle: General Chamber of Commerce approves bill from Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz raising contribution ratio
news_8.newsText:
On the night of 18th, the Kazimierz General Chamber of Commerce unanimously voted to pass an amendment to the Corporate Contribution Act proposed by the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz. Starting next year, the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz will raise the corporate contribution ratio across the board in some territories. The additional funds raised will be put towards the military budget for several dozen campaign knightclubs including the Silverlance Pegasus Knightclub. This move can be seen as a countermeasure against Ursus's increasing military activities. 
At the same time, some managing directors from the General Chamber of Commerce raised a proposal for large corporations to collectively form a 'Security Force', to keep the peace in the Kazimierz Major and the various city-states. This proposal was rejected by the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz.

Today, the Mieszko Group, Rose Paper Union and other companies raised a formal complaint against the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz. The representative for the collective claimed that the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz ordered the mobilization of some campaign knights on its own discretion, without going through the legal process with the National Council. On the other hand, the Grand Knight's staff in the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz believes that the mobilization of the campaign knights is a legitimate function accorded to the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz in times of emergency, and that the move was well within their rights. 
The General Chamber of Commerce continued to demand the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz give a reasonable answer, while the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz insisted that as the highest judicial organ of Kazimierz, the National Council is not beholden to the General Chamber of Commerce, no matter what issues arise between the National Council and the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz. 
Later on, the representative from the Mieszko Group accused the Knights Association of mishandling the Radiant Knight incident, and demanded alterations to the spokesperson system and some duties of the Knights Association. This move displeased some of the knightly nobility, though the General Chamber of Commerce indicated that revoking the amendment to the Corporate Contribution Act remains a distinct possibility. The meeting is currently still in session.

news_2.newsTitle: The Radiant Knight appears once more? Will the debuting knight of the Nearl family restore honor to the nobility?
news_2.newsText:
<newsimg>newsTextPic_2_1<newsimg/>
The preliminaries of the Kazimierz Major have been ongoing for several months now. Besides the seven Knightclubs directly invited to join the Major and the four Knight Orders, the remaining knights have been competing against one another to accumulate points in the preliminaries. 
However, an unexpected contestant appeared yesterday in the West Division's Roar Arena——Maria Nearl. This is a big deal for any knightwatcher. 
<newsimg>newsTextPic_2_2<newsimg/>
Six years ago, the Radiant Knight who shot to fame after winning the championship was expelled when it was discovered she had concealed her infection, causing the old and once prestigious family to fall into the awkward situation of not having a presiding Knight Primus. Back then, Młynar Nearl who was pushed to the forefront refused the Knights Association's invitation, and the Nearl family was on the brink of losing their noble status. 
In the end, the National Council declared that should the Nearl family not present a new Knight Primus with a legitimate title within five years, they would be stripped of their nobility. Maria Nearl's performance in the current season will determine the fate of the Nearl family. 
We will watch this young knight closely.

news_3.newsTitle: More than a hundred knights join the banquet held by the Northwood Order!
news_3.newsText:
The name 'Northwood' should not be unfamiliar to any knight who follows the Kazimierz Major. As one of the Knight Orders of Kazimierz and still in its prime, there are many veteran Knightclubs under its banner such as the Bladehelm Knightclub and the Spikeshield Knightclub. With no other Knightclubs promoted to Knight Orders this year, Northwood has managed to maintain their hold on the Central Division, but the situation remains dismal as the Knight Orders of the other Divisions continue to eye them eagerly. 
<newsimg>newsTextPic_3_1<newsimg/>
The stated objective of the banquet is to celebrate the several new knight contestants, but it is easy to ascertain that more than half the invited knights are unaffiliated and even untitled independent knights. Obviously, to continue remaining an 'Order' and avoid falling to the status of a 'Club', Northwood has decided to expand during the current season to avoid a poor showing. We watch with bated breath to see how many are attracted by the promised cake.

news_4.newsTitle: Qualitative Report on the Suborning of Infected: Kindness does not imply indulgence
news_4.newsText:
This year is the third since the inception of the Infected Participation System. We are extremely happy to announce that this humanitarian initiative has achieved significant results, with Infected-related incidents dropping substantially in many areas. The comportment of the Infected fighting for their lives has won them unique respect as well as tangible wealth they require for survival.  
<newsimg>newsTextPic_4_1<newsimg/>
However, as the number of Infected participants increases year-on-year, problems have inevitably cropped up. Besides the challenge of getting proper treatment to Infected knights, some Infected who have attained great wealth through competitions and their fighting skills have begun to buy over their Infected kin and set up private organizations unrecognized by the Knights Association. These organizations are heavily suspected to be involved in illegal fundraising and holding armed rallies with the goal of disrupting social stability and taking revenge against non-Infected. 
Currently, the Knights Association has filed a legal complaint to the National Council requesting to remedy the problem of Infected knights taking in large numbers of illegal Infected. Kazimierz will never allow the 'Great Kawalerielki Separation' incident to happen ever again.

news_6.newsTitle: '10 Years in the making' Mid-Tournament Special Report
news_6.newsText:
After approval by the Knights Association and a unanimous vote from the National Council, the Tyrell Knightclub which has long been sponsored by the Ellen Select Technology Co. and a fierce contender within the Top 100 Knightclubs has finally been promoted to a Knight Order. Currently, there are only two Knightclubs under the banner of the Tyrell Knight Order: The Rachel Knightclub composed of the original members and renamed after the leader's surname, and the Warwhip Knightclub responsible for training young reserve knights. Though they are lacking in numbers, the addition of the former second runner-up Frost Skull Knight as an instructor in the Warwhip Knightclub has made waves. 
<newsimg>newsTextPic_6_1<newsimg/>
At the same time, with the approval of the Knights Association, the first superstar of the current season has emerged even before the preliminaries have ended, receiving a knight's title after yesterday evening's match. With her outstanding ability, incredibly high number of votes and rapidly rising point ranking, independent knight Justyna managed to attract the attention of many companies, earning her the title of 'Fartooth' early this morning. 
No matter if it's 'Fartooth' Justyna or Tyrell Knight Order, all of this signifies the outstanding development of the Kazimierz competition industry. We look forward to seeing what new trends will come from this season of the Kazimierz Major.

news_7.newsTitle: Nearl's Secret Base? Secret Bar Exposed! You Won't Believe Which Knights Drink Here!
news_7.newsText:
At the end of Golden Feather Street, there is an unassuming bar with a strange name——Scary Martin. Such bars can be found all over Kazimierz, but this one is unique for one particular reason most people are unaware of. This bar's regular clientele are almost all retired knights. 
<newsimg>newsTextPic_7_1<newsimg/>
That isn't what's important, though. The real story is the Radiant Knight's sister Maria Nearl and the Whislash Knight Zofia, who are often in the area after the bar closes. Most bars don't close so early, and it's a bit of a stretch to say that it's because of bad business. But Maria and Whislash have been frequently seen near the bar. I'm sure everyone is familiar with Maria, and as an independent knight her relationship with Whislash was once a hot topic. Even after Maria joined the Major representing the Nearl family, Młynar Nearl, who was once pushed for the same position kept quiet. According to his coworkers, he has paid no attention to it and is still working an ordinary job, as if he has nothing to do with it. 
Perhaps the secret behind the Nearl family lies within this bar. Your correspondent has no other information to report for now, but readers who wish to witness the Nearls' grace may want to try their luck.

news_8.newsTitle: General Chamber of Commerce approves bill from Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz raising contribution ratio
news_8.newsText:
On the night of 18th, the Kazimierz General Chamber of Commerce unanimously voted to pass an amendment to the Corporate Contribution Act proposed by the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz. Starting next year, the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz will raise the corporate contribution ratio across the board in some territories. The additional funds raised will be put towards the military budget for several dozen military Knightclubs including the Silverlance Pegasus Knightclub. This move can be seen as a countermeasure against Ursus's increasing military activities. 
At the same time, some managing directors from the General Chamber of Commerce raised a proposal for large corporations to collectively form a 'Security Force', to keep the peace in the Kazimierz Major and the various city-states. This proposal was rejected by the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz.

news_9.newsTitle: Rebellion and ignorance of the new generation——Seven rising stars reject all invitations from Knightclubs
news_9.newsText:
Yesterday afternoon, the Fartooth Knight rejected invitations from multiple corporations for the third time, and publicly expressed her intention to establish an 'Independent Knightclub.' Simultaneously, the popular independent knight Maria Nearl rejected invitations from corporations such as the Słoma Food Company. The rising Infected Knightclub 'Pinus Sylvestris' also stated that they will not be entering into a partnership with any corporation. Things being what they are, one can't help but wonder: With the rapid development of knight sports, does this pursuit of 'freedom' and these attempts to restore the 'glory of knights' in peacetime highlight the ignorance and naivety of this new generation of young knights? 
The relationship between Knightclub and sponsor is symbiotic, sharing in both the glory and failures. Ever since the implementation of the First Decree centuries ago, knights have enjoyed the respect of the populace. With the rapid development of Kazimierz, knights must also find a proper path forward in the new era. As for these disruptors among the young knights, perhaps spokesperson McKee describes them best: 'a heartbreaking misunderstanding.'

news_12.newsText:
Forty minutes ago, the exiled Margaret Nearl (henceforth referred to as the Radiant Knight) suddenly appeared in the Fireblade Arena, interrupting the ongoing contest in full view of millions of viewers. What is going on? 
According to sources, there were multiple issues during the special 2V2 battle being held in the Fireblade Arena. Firstly, the Fartooth Knight was unable to participate due to the recent incident and Maria Nearl was forced to fight alone against the Snowyheel Knightclub. As for the Snowyheel Knightclub, they had temporarily accepted the Corrupted Knight and Withered Knight right before the match and decided then to send the both of them into battle. As the battle got into full swing, the Radiant Knight suddenly rushed into the arena, rescuing her nearly defeated sister and turning the tides. 
The exiled are forbidden from entering any Kazimierz city. Though Infected are now allowed to participate, and the crowd's enthusiasm for the Radiant Knight remains as clear as ever. How will the National Council and the Knights Association respond? Are we witnessing the continuation of the legend? Can the Radiant Knight's 'lucky miracles' truly defeat her mighty opponents? 
Will the Radiant Knight bring about new miracles, or will this blatant disregard for the Knights Association invite swift retaliation? As countless readers wait with bated breath, we strive to bring you the latest developments!

news_13.newsTitle: Knights Association and National Council seeking public opinion
news_13.newsText:
This afternoon, the Radiant Knight returned to Kawalerielki and intervened in the battle between Maria and the Snowyheel Knightclub, causing a great uproar across the media and our viewers. After extensive discussions between the Knights Association and the spokesperson representative, it was agreed that the Radiant Knight's intervention in the battle was a clear violation of the rules, but due to the multiple violations from the two knights of the Snowyheel Knightclub as well, the match is invalid. 
At the same time, the Knights Association raised a complaint to the National Council. The National Council will soon hold an emergency meeting to decide the status of the Radiant Knight's knighthood. If the Radiant Knight is acknowledged, the lack of a Knight Primus will no longer plague the Nearl family.

news_14.newsTitle: Live: Several Managing Directors of the General Chamber of Commerce protest against the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz
news_14.newsText:
Today, the Mieszko Group, Rose Paper Union and other companies raised a formal complaint against the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz. The representative for the collective claimed that the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz ordered the mobilization of some warrior-knights on its own discretion, without going through the legal process with the National Council. On the other hand, the Grand Knight's staff in the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz believes that the mobilization of the warrior-knights is a legitimate function accorded to the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz in times of emergency, and that the move was well within their rights. 
The General Chamber of Commerce continued to demand the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz give a reasonable answer, while the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz insisted that as the highest judicial organ of Kazimierz, the National Council is not beholden to the General Chamber of Commerce, no matter what issues arise between the National Council and the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz. 
Later on, the representative from the Mieszko Group accused the Knights Association of mishandling the Radiant Knight incident, and demanded alterations to the spokesperson system and some duties of the Knights Association. This move displeased some of the knightly nobility, though the General Chamber of Commerce indicated that revoking the amendment to the Corporate Contribution Act remains a distinct possibility. The meeting is currently still in session.

news_15.newsText:
Dear Ms. Amiya:

I am pleased to inform you that the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz and Knights Association agreed yesterday to pass the 'Terms of Cooperation for Treatment of Infected Contestants & Medical Environment Rectification' bill proposed by your company. The electronic contract is attached to this email, and a contact will be visiting your office soon. 
As a representative of the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz, I hereby send my regards to Miss Amiya and the members of the Medical Department in your company. The other medical and pharmaceutical companies involved in this project are extremely happy to receive your help, as we are all warmed by the virtue of assisting those in need. 
At the same time, please allow me to extend my personal thanks to Miss Amiya, Miss Kal'tsit and the 'Doctor.' 
Thank you for accepting and sheltering the Radiant Knight during her unjust exile. I guarantee, upon my honor as the Grand Knight of the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz, that Nearl will be treated fairly. 
                                                                        May Glory Live On. 

                                                                                                        Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz

pic_01.picDesc:
Taken by a journalist who happened to be passing by.
Ch'en had believed that this case was resolved by one of her local Dossoles counterparts, until she saw this photo in the papers by chance, two days after the competition ended.

pic_03.picName: Taken in front of Dossoles S.P.A. Boutique
pic_03.picDesc:
Fell from Tequila's luggage by chance.
It seems to have been taken while his friend was helping him shut down his weapons shop. The competition has ended, he has lost his job, his status and even his home, but he looks far more relaxed than before.

pic_02.picName: Taken in front of A.H.C. Bar
pic_02.picDesc:
The headlines of the Dossoles Daily's Entertainment section that day.
Ch'en found herself at the A.H.C. Bar after following the clues, where Lin Yühsia happened to be as well. She admits that Lin Yühsia's methods are far more direct and effective, but she still thinks that they aren't right.

pic_04.picDesc:
Swire's favorite photo from this vacation.
After the four met up, Hoshiguma and Swire joined Ch'en's investigation in Dossoles. As for why Lin Yühsia is present? Just look at her expression.

pic_06.picName: Taken during the Rhodes Island Office's ribbon-cutting ceremony
pic_06.picDesc:
Mayor Candela was sufficiently impressed by Ch'en's results. The construction of the office was approved and it will receive the support of the city council.
Ch'en is quite stupefied by the entire matter.

pic_05.picDesc:
Hoshiguma forcibly drags Ch'en in front of the camera.
With the conclusion of Ch'en's investigation, her holiday at Dossoles has come to an end. Ch'en's thoughts remain firmly focused on the city. She has yet to find an answer, but she seems to have gained direction.

EMPTY.dialog: You two, don't look down on those Mama John's vouchers I've prepared for you. At Mama John's, you can buy almost anything you've ever wished for.
What happens to the recycled stickers? Don't worry, there are many collectors within this city. They'll pay a pretty penny for these things.
In theory, I should provide all services free of charge for you two... I hope Madam Candela doesn't blame me for this.

LOW.dialog: Good progress, Miss Ch'en. If you have no interest in wine, coffee isn't a bad choice either. Dossoles is famed for both its wine and coffee.
As expected of Miss Lin, there's quite a lot here. It seems that you're partial to wine? It appears you're more suited to this city than I first believed.
I must say, the two of you are working well together... Ah, please ignore me. This is just a coincidence. Right, a coincidence.

MEDIUM.dialog: Could it be that you two are the type that hoards all your stuff and refuses to throw them out even if they're useless?
A fruitful bounty, Miss Ch'en. Hmm? Why are there so many Leithanien and Columbian businesses? It's because Madam Candela does not care about that.
Miss Lin, I suppose you have already built your own network for processing these? As expected of the daughter of the Rat King...... Hmm? Your father has many fans here.

HIGH.dialog: Miss Ch'en, you might drive some collectors crazy if they were to look at your collection right now. Oh, it's far more likely that these are all worthless by tomorrow, though.
Forgive me, Miss Lin. I have already cleared out my other warehouse just to store your loot...... Fine, I still have three warehouses I can use. As long as you're happy.
To be frank, you two should open a collectibles shop. If you ever intend to act on that idea, please let me know immediately. I'll sell my shop and invest all my savings in you.

GACHA.dialog: Without noticing, you two have already gathered so many collectibles. I've prepared a small gift for you, hopefully it will help you on your journey of collection.

principalDescList: Don't you folks feel ever feel alienated, going by codenames all the time? I hope you'll call me Senomy one day. It's way more intimate that way, heehee~
Need something from me? Just ask away. I'll try to satisfy your wishes, whatever they might be~
Silently watching over others is one of the joys of being a protector. Oh, sorry about that, I didn't mean to call myself your protector. Hehe, I'll watch my tone next time~
So you're this affectionate with everyone, huh? Mmm... Seems like laying you bare won't be an easy task. But that's alright, I enjoy a challenge~
This brand upon my flesh also represents a warning to myself. After all, a brand upon the soul is far more terrifying.
Remember that Platinum belongs to the Armorless Union, and is a pawn of the General Chamber. Please be more careful the next time you see her.
'Look for an opportunity to help that hooded guest into a change of clothes.' ––That's what our Master said. Well, actually, that was actually what I wanted to say. Heehee~
Well met, Doctor of Rhodes Island.
We will not take off our helmets without the approval of the Grandmaster. Such is the ironclad law of the campaign knights.
Apologies, but we are also not allowed to privately disclose our names to others.
Please refrain from touching my weapon. Thank you.
As long as we are here, your safety in the Grand Knight Territory is guaranteed. The General Chamber of Commerce shall not lay a finger on you.

Are you curious about the duties and responsibilities of a campaign knight? About that... Please allow me to consult the Grandmaster for instructions. She will decide whether or not that question can be answered.
We are campaign knights, but the Grand Knight Territory is not our home.
The Major will be over shortly, but Kazimierz is no less of a powder keg, Doctor of Rhodes Island. The days to come, are certain to be long indeed...
Just as the sun is sure to rise, the members of the Nearl clan will never let us down.
It's not as if we're having a public dialogue, Doctor. Please relax - there's no need to be so nervous.
Only the campaign knights call me by 'Grandmaster.' It is our internal courtesy, and can be considered a useful part of our heritage.
Ioleta Russell, Chairman of the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz. It's a pleasure to work with you.
Mature children like Sona are rare these days, but when I look into her eyes and think of the pain she has endured... I don't think I'm qualified to comfort her.

Gravel is an outstanding seedling worthy of cultivation. I hope that Rhodes Island, and you in particular, can give her the treatment she deserves... I can see that she really wants to stay on Rhodes Island. Am I wrong?
I am Spokesman Malkiewicz's, err... Mr. Malkiewicz's assistant, Jewell. You can just call me J if you'd like...

Th-That's right! I had the great privilege of working under Master Malkiewicz in the past, which is why I even have this opportunity now... In order to repay Master Malkiewicz's kindness, I shall work even harder!

Doctor, do you have any requests? I can introduce products to you, help plan your travel routes, sort through your itinerary, or... Oh, just a cup of water? Y-Yes, right away, I'll have that for you in a moment.

My dream is to finally get the Outstanding Employee Award after twenty years of work. I heard that employees given that honor can get a 1% lifetime discount on all of the company's products. That's far too generous, I say.

There's still room for improvement in this report? No, uh, I understand... It's just that, could I have a bit more time? ...Y-Yes, I understand, I'll have it ready first thing tomorrow morning... I'm sorry, Doctor, is there anything else you need?
I fell asleep?! Oh, oh no... I'm so sorry, Doctor... Were there any phone calls just now? ...Good, good, sorry for inconveniencing you... I, I'll go wash my face. I'll get back to work right away...

After Major-related affairs have concluded, your company will be setting off for another country, right? Ah, I see. Thank you for your recent tutelage, Doctor. I will always remember the things you've taught me, and I wish you and your company the best of luck.
You've done well to follow the stipulations of our contract. But, the General Chamber hopes you do not do more than necessary, Doctor.

I am McKee, a spokesman for the General Chamber of Commerce. I'm working with Malkiewicz to relay issues raised by the General Chamber of Commerce during the Major. I hope our relationship will be a fruitful one.
Madam Droste has her own rules for life, and even I, as someone responsible for her PR, have no right to judge.

During Rhodes Island's stay in the Grand Knight Territory, the General Chamber of Commerce may ask for your cooperation in matters outside of dispensing medicine. Whether you decide to complete these requests is up to you, though know that we will be evaluating your company's performance.
If you wish to apply for free passage through the Grand Knight Territory, please also inform the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz that the General Chamber of Commerce lacks the applicable authority.

I'm only here to convey to you the resolutions of the General Chamber of Commerce. If you want to discuss specific matters, please speak to Malkiewicz, who is chiefly responsible for being your liaison.

The General Chamber of Commerce will cooperate with the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz to ensure that the Major is held in a fair and just manner... What's the meaning of that expression you're making?

Within the scope of the law and agreements of the General Chamber of Commerce, I will fight for the rights of the Infected as much as possible. Thus, I need your advice on an update pertaining to the specifics of the Infected Knights Accommodation Plan.
There will always be things that cannot be achieved through formal procedures, so the General Chamber of Commerce requires the Armorless Union to resolve those problems.
Even if Nearl wins the championships, Kazimierz will not undergo any groundbreaking changes. She will still be playing by the rules rather than breaking them, and that's the best proof.
This isn't our first time meeting, esteemed Doctor. Allow me to reintroduce myself - I am Spokesman Malkiewicz of the General Chamber of Commerce, but you can simply call me Malkiewicz.

Just a few months ago, I was nothing more than a small-time salaryman who joined the company after bankruptcy - and now, I'm a spokesman for the General Chamber of Commerce. This may have something to do with my ability, but between that and opportunity... I'd say opportunity had a bigger part to play. In Kazimierz, anything is possible.

After the Major ends, the spokesmen receive a hefty bonus, then lose that status and return to their prior company and position. As for where I'll be going to work... Sorry, Doctor, but I'm not quite sure about that myself.
You can trust me, just as you trust your operators. Should you encounter any difficulties, please give me a call or write me a letter. As soon as I hear from you, I'll reply as soon as possible.
Ugh... I can't do this anymore... What a pain in the ass... Maybe I'll just ask for unpaid leave...
*sigh*... I'm still on vacation... You want to go on a stroll? I guess that's fine.
It's nothing. I simply wanted to see the extent of your capabilities, Doctor of Rhodes Island.
Don't stick your nose where it doesn't belong, or it'll be hard to say whether you'll be able to leave the Grand Knight Territory alive. Ugh... Why am I even wasting the effort to tell you this...
Gotta lay off the sweets... Maybe hold off on the fruit juice too... If I end up out of shape, the damage to my image will be irreconcilable.
The purpose of work is to put food on the table. What else would it be? ...I'm off now, so bye.
If you Rhodes Island people didn't cause extra trouble for me that one day... Well, whatever, just an idle thought. We stand on different sides anyway.
Please take a look at the collaborative matters between our two companies. If you have any questions or concerns, I'll report them as soon as possible.
If you don't have any other questions, then I will take my leave. There are still other company meetings for me to attend to.
The way you treat the Infected... Ah, don't worry about it.
Pardon me for not answering any questions related to my family. It's not work-related.
Head to work, do my job, get off work, go home. My life isn't so different from that of any ordinary person in Kazimierz.
I, Młynar Nearl, am contacting Rhodes Island on behalf of our company. This is my business card - please have a look.
Toland? No, I didn't know him particularly well.

'Flamelung' and 'Yellow Smog' were good brothers to me. Their inexplicable deaths brought me much sorrow. By the way, this matter may be somewhat related to you folks. I heard they were cut down by an Ægir woman with a single stroke of the sword. Does that ring a bell?

A meeting is a convergence of fates, and looking at this fate, why not add an extra zero to the reward? Hmm... Haha, I didn't expect you to also be a bit of a jokester. I didn't mean adding it to the beginning...
You paid, that makes you my boss for the time being, and hopefully we enjoy our time working together. So, what do you need done?
In order to survive, you do have to take your outward appearance into consideration. I must say, being short a pair of horns spares a significant amount of hassle.
I'm just a no-name bounty hunter, doing some dirty work for a living. Now, I've called some of my brothers together to get some stuff done. So, how about it, Doctor? Think we can strike a deal?

principalDescList: Don't you folks feel ever feel alienated, going by codenames all the time? I hope you'll call me Senomy one day. It's way more intimate that way, heehee~
Need something from me? Just ask away. I'll try to satisfy your wishes, whatever they might be~
Silently watching over others is one of the joys of being a protector. Oh, sorry about that, I didn't mean to call myself your protector. Hehe, I'll watch my tone next time~
So you're this affectionate with everyone, huh? Mmm... Seems like laying you bare won't be an easy task. But that's alright, I enjoy a challenge~
This brand upon my flesh also represents a warning to myself. After all, a brand upon the soul is far more terrifying.
Remember that Platinum belongs to the Armorless Union, and is a pawn of the General Chamber. Please be more careful the next time you see her.
'Look for an opportunity to help that hooded guest into a change of clothes.' ––That's what our Master said. Well, actually, that was actually what I wanted to say. Heehee~
Well met, Doctor of Rhodes Island.
We will not take off our helmets without the approval of the Grandmaster. Such is the ironclad law of the campaign knights.
Apologies, but we are also not allowed to privately disclose our names to others.
Please refrain from touching my weapon. Thank you.
As long as we are here, your safety in the Grand Knight Territory is guaranteed. The General Chamber of Commerce shall not lay a finger on you.

Are you curious about the duties and responsibilities of a campaign knight? About that... Please allow me to consult the Grandmaster for instructions. She will decide whether or not that question can be answered.
We are campaign knights, but the Grand Knight Territory is not our home.
The Major will be over shortly, but Kazimierz is no less of a powder keg, Doctor of Rhodes Island. The days to come, are certain to be long indeed...
Just as the sun is sure to rise, the members of the Nearl clan will never let us down.
It's not as if we're having a public dialogue, Doctor. Please relax - there's no need to be so nervous.
Only the campaign knights call me by 'Grandmaster.' It is our internal courtesy, and can be considered a useful part of our heritage.
Ioleta Russell, Chairman of the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz. It's a pleasure to work with you.
Mature children like Sona are rare these days, but when I look into her eyes and think of the pain she has endured... I don't think I'm qualified to comfort her.

Gravel is an outstanding seedling worthy of cultivation. I hope that Rhodes Island, and you in particular, can give her the treatment she deserves... I can see that she really wants to stay on Rhodes Island. Am I wrong?
I am Spokesman Malkiewicz's, err... Mr. Malkiewicz's assistant, Jewell. You can just call me J if you'd like...

Th-That's right! I had the great privilege of working under Master Malkiewicz in the past, which is why I even have this opportunity now... In order to repay Master Malkiewicz's kindness, I shall work even harder!

Doctor, do you have any requests? I can introduce products to you, help plan your travel routes, sort through your itinerary, or... Oh, just a cup of water? Y-Yes, right away, I'll have that for you in a moment.

My dream is to finally get the Outstanding Employee Award after twenty years of work. I heard that employees given that honor can get a 1% lifetime discount on all of the company's products. That's far too generous, I say.

There's still room for improvement in this report? No, uh, I understand... It's just that, could I have a bit more time? ...Y-Yes, I understand, I'll have it ready first thing tomorrow morning... I'm sorry, Doctor, is there anything else you need?
I fell asleep?! Oh, oh no... I'm so sorry, Doctor... Were there any phone calls just now? ...Good, good, sorry for inconveniencing you... I, I'll go wash my face. I'll get back to work right away...

After Major-related affairs have concluded, your company will be setting off for another country, right? Ah, I see. Thank you for your recent tutelage, Doctor. I will always remember the things you've taught me, and I wish you and your company the best of luck.
You've done well to follow the stipulations of our contract. But, the General Chamber hopes you do not do more than necessary, Doctor.

I am McKee, a spokesman for the General Chamber of Commerce. I'm working with Malkiewicz to relay issues raised by the General Chamber of Commerce during the Major. I hope our relationship will be a fruitful one.
Madam Droste has her own rules for life, and even I, as someone responsible for her PR, have no right to judge.

During Rhodes Island's stay in the Grand Knight Territory, the General Chamber of Commerce may ask for your cooperation in matters outside of dispensing medicine. Whether you decide to complete these requests is up to you, though know that we will be evaluating your company's performance.
If you wish to apply for free passage through the Grand Knight Territory, please also inform the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz that the General Chamber of Commerce lacks the applicable authority.

I'm only here to convey to you the resolutions of the General Chamber of Commerce. If you want to discuss specific matters, please speak to Malkiewicz, who is chiefly responsible for being your liaison.

The General Chamber of Commerce will cooperate with the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz to ensure that the Major is held in a fair and just manner... What's the meaning of that expression you're making?

Within the scope of the law and agreements of the General Chamber of Commerce, I will fight for the rights of the Infected as much as possible. Thus, I need your advice on an update pertaining to the specifics of the Infected Knights Accommodation Plan.
There will always be things that cannot be achieved through formal procedures, so the General Chamber of Commerce requires the Armorless Union to resolve those problems.
Even if Nearl wins the championships, Kazimierz will not undergo any groundbreaking changes. She will still be playing by the rules rather than breaking them, and that's the best proof.
This isn't our first time meeting, esteemed Doctor. Allow me to reintroduce myself - I am Spokesman Malkiewicz of the General Chamber of Commerce, but you can simply call me Malkiewicz.

Just a few months ago, I was nothing more than a small-time salaryman who joined the company after bankruptcy - and now, I'm a spokesman for the General Chamber of Commerce. This may have something to do with my ability, but between that and opportunity... I'd say opportunity had a bigger part to play. In Kazimierz, anything is possible.

After the Major ends, the spokesmen receive a hefty bonus, then lose that status and return to their prior company and position. As for where I'll be going to work... Sorry, Doctor, but I'm not quite sure about that myself.
You can trust me, just as you trust your operators. Should you encounter any difficulties, please give me a call or write me a letter. As soon as I hear from you, I'll reply as soon as possible.
Ugh... I can't do this anymore... What a pain in the ass... Maybe I'll just ask for unpaid leave...
*sigh*... I'm still on vacation... You want to go on a stroll? I guess that's fine.
It's nothing. I simply wanted to see the extent of your capabilities, Doctor of Rhodes Island.
Don't stick your nose where it doesn't belong, or it'll be hard to say whether you'll be able to leave the Grand Knight Territory alive. Ugh... Why am I even wasting the effort to tell you this...
Gotta lay off the sweets... Maybe hold off on the fruit juice too... If I end up out of shape, the damage to my image will be irreconcilable.
The purpose of work is to put food on the table. What else would it be? ...I'm off now, so bye.
If you Rhodes Island people didn't cause extra trouble for me that one day... Well, whatever, just an idle thought. We stand on different sides anyway.
Please take a look at the collaborative matters between our two companies. If you have any questions or concerns, I'll report them as soon as possible.
If you don't have any other questions, then I will take my leave. There are still other company meetings for me to attend to.
The way you treat the Infected... Ah, don't worry about it.
Pardon me for not answering any questions related to my family. It's not work-related.
Head to work, do my job, get off work, go home. My life isn't so different from that of any ordinary person in Kazimierz.
I, Młynar Nearl, am contacting Rhodes Island on behalf of our company. This is my business card - please have a look.
Toland? No, I didn't know him particularly well.

'Flamelung' and 'Yellow Smog' were good brothers to me. Their inexplicable deaths brought me much sorrow. By the way, this matter may be somewhat related to you folks. I heard they were cut down by an Ægir woman with a single stroke of the sword. Does that ring a bell?

A meeting is a convergence of fates, and looking at this fate, why not add an extra zero to the reward? Hmm... Haha, I didn't expect you to also be a bit of a jokester. I didn't mean adding it to the beginning...
You paid, that makes you my boss for the time being, and hopefully we enjoy our time working together. So, what do you need done?
In order to survive, you do have to take your outward appearance into consideration. I must say, being short a pair of horns spares a significant amount of hassle.
I'm just a no-name bounty hunter, doing some dirty work for a living. Now, I've called some of my brothers together to get some stuff done. So, how about it, Doctor? Think we can strike a deal?
Bounty hunters mainly care about getting their next meal, and might not use their real names when going from place to place. But if you insist, hmm... Ah, right, you can call me Toland Cash.
Młynar? Heh, I know that guy way too well. Since our partnership's going smoothly, I can give you some info on him for a friendly price.

landmarkDesList: This road has already become scantly traveled. Nobody cares about the stories that once unfolded here, nobody remains to record them. Silence falls upon all equally, bringing the same quietude. Only the street sign marks these memories, roughly engraved with the name of this small town— 'Gran Faro.'

Nobody knows why this lighthouse survived the disaster, but perhaps it is because no matter how terrifying the wind and waves may be, nothing can stop people from gazing towards the sea. Iberia's eyes will never close, only be temporarily clouded over.

When disaster struck, both the great flagship Stultifera Navis—the Ship of Fools—and the Iberian fleet to which it belonged were out at sea. Giant waves swallowed everything, but the ghosts of the past still lingered.

The huge dome elevator in the middle of the Stultifera connects the various levels of this great battleship. When riding it, one may witness Iberia's breathtaking scenery depicted across the walls. Standing here is like standing in the center of the world.
On the main deck, the nethersea brand is spreading. It mercilessly engulfs everything, irreversibly. This is how it survives, able to heal wounds left even by the passage of time.
This part of the ocean may have had a name once, but that no longer matters. The premise for a name to be born is that something needs to be distinguished. But now, the ocean is the ocean.

storyDesList: He threw a question into the ancient, bottomless well, and received an answer in return.
He grew up along the coast. He longed for the freedom to see the ocean.
Along the uninhabited street, travelers from afar now sing.
On the long road beside the ocean, the representatives of two civilizations speak herein.
It shuts its eyes, its sweet dreams unperturbed for over a decade.
His eyes widened with anger, his hand not letting go of the helm for decades.
Come as you please, leave in pieces. Freely does wine pour, bodies litter the floor.
There is no road ahead, as far as the eyes can see.
The Seaborn never see their own as enemies. This is a behavior unique to humans.
The unbearable past relentlessly chases him. The unfaceable future solemnly awaits him.
How should one sort out one's thoughts, when reuniting with a mortal enemy after a long absence? Share a dance.
Pack your bags, and return to the starting point. The road ahead is still long.

treasureDesList: 'What the hell was that? Why is this happening to Gran Faro? First the Ægir, then the cultists, and now these damned monsters! I need to leave this place! Otherwise... Otherwise...!'
'I've seen it with my own eyes! The Inquisition's flames will burn a person's soul dry!'
'I leave these things to you!'

Sheds still line the shores, offering a glimpse of how bustling this small town used to be. People from all over used to arrive, trying to restore a glimmer of hope following the calamity. But now, it's been abandoned, its sheets of metal rusting away. The precious materials once used to build this place are now scattered about everywhere, no longer of anyone's concern.

This place may have been inhabited by Ægir Islanders, as the signboards bear faintly-visible patterns distinct from the Iberian style. Now, it is completely uninhabited. And when the previous inhabitants left, they lacked the time to even take their supplies with them.
This is the lighthouse the elders spoke of, the 'Eye of Iberia' in Jordi's dreams. These corridors, stairs, and panels may once have been tread upon and touched by his parents.

Jordi tries to feel an aura of familiarity from them. Countless times, he has sketched his parents' likenesses from his imagination, the way they would shuttle between lighthouses. Those few notes left behind correspond to reality, line by line.

Perhaps their bones are still interred somewhere in this lighthouse. The thought makes Jordi shudder. Now he stands at the same place, his hand covering the same control panel. Where, then, will fate take him?
Jordi decides not to think about these things. He must accomplish his duties, irrespective of his identity, his worth, or his beliefs.
Jordi stands here for the sake of his unrealistic dreams, and though he may be anxious and uncertain, the one thing he is not, is lost.
The warehouse holds supplies designated for the next voyage. The only problem? Nobody knows when that will be, or if it will ever happen.

In a half-opened safe sits an outdated nautical chart, once used by the old Iberian fleet to conquer the seas. The crystallization of their explorations through the mist. Unfortunately, it is now nothing more than scrap paper. A few other miscellaneous items also sit at the bottom of the safe, with nobody left to use them.

Inside the bathroom, everything looks good as new, and drops of water dribble from the spigot. The only unusual thing is that all the mirrors have been shattered, now only able to reflect broken images. There are still unused supplies in the storage box under the sink.

A storage room full of spare sails. Unfold one, and you will find a canvas decorated with golden threads, and carefully embroidered with the pattern of the Iberian flag. Maybe there are some useful supplies to be found here.

The anchor system was completely destroyed during the Profound Silence, and this cabin has been empty for many years. However, someone seems to have turned this place into their own secret stash, leaving behind quite a few glittering things.

The drafting room was once used to aggregate the results of exploration and draft nautical charts. After the calamity, the entire ocean's currents, prevailing winds, and uncharted islands all underwent tremendous changes, rendering the laws formulated over generations completely meaningless. Some usable supplies can still be found here.

Nobody knows what these discarded barrels were once used for. Perhaps over six decades ago, they were filled with spirits that the crew would drink in celebration. Now only a few tattered relics sit at the bottom of the barrel. Who was the desperate seaman who exchanged these things for the last sip of wine?

The Penal Battalion shows no weakness. The Penal Battalion shall not yield. The Penal Battalion is Iberia's bastion, and even the terrible waves do nothing more than wash away any impurities. From this supply station, the soldiers stare at the Iberian soil now swallowed by the ocean.
'These days, I will occasionally dream. Of dazzling golden domes, of my humid hometown.'
'I have never felt water in this form before—soft, cold, beautiful, and deadly.'
'These flames blaze more passionately than any I have felt before, perhaps because my partner in this conversation is that extraordinary.'
'Breogan brought with him not only dreams of gold, but also a warning from the sea. Most people chose to ignore the latter.'
'Nobody can resist their own desires, especially when you understand when they are desiring.'
'Where there is light, there is also a shadow. The brighter the light, the deeper the darkness.'
'As a friend, Alfonso is absolutely qualified. As a captain... Fine, there isn't anyone to compare him to anyway.'
This piece of paper has been waterlogged for so long that the letters on it are no longer legible.
'Soil is the cradle of life. They say that when the spring wind blows, green shoots will sprout here.'
'I can feel the excitement in each and every one of us. We are about to face a cornerstone of the truth.'
'Those with power tend to underestimate their ability. Even more so for those with great power.'
'Once ambition germinates, it knows only how to proliferate. Even if it's clear it will only lead to ruin.'
'Do you hear the sound of the tides? It's as if someone is sobbing.'
'Friends, we are all starting to get old. Yesterday, Breogan spent half the day complaining about his new wrinkles. I think it's because he frowns too much.'
'...Leviathan...Ægir...lost...Abyssal Hunters... This plan is our last hope.'
